Package: rfret
Title: Analyze FRET Binding Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Guillaume", "Gaullier",
           email = "guillaume@gaullier.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "dtc"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3405-6021")),
    person("Tiana", "Stastny", role = "ctb"),
    person("Ben", "Jenkins", role = "ctb"),
    person("Andrew", "Blumenfeld", role = "ctb"),
    person("Raibatak", "Das", role = "ctb"),
    person("Karolin", "Luger", role = c("ldr", "fnd"))
    )
Description: This package provides functions to analyze FRET binding data.
    Given raw fluorescence data from a FRET titration experiment's donor,
    acceptor and FRET channels, it allows to: (1) plot all channels to visually
    inspect raw data; (2) correct FRET signal; (3) estimate parameters of the
    quadratic binding equation (Kd, signal_min, signal_max); (4) fit the
    quadratic binding equation to the data; (5) report Kd; and (6) plot the
    corrected FRET and resulting binding curve.
